1 crea ted in Section 256 of Title 62 of the Oklahoma Statutes, the sum
2 of Two Million Dollars ($2,000,000.00) for the purpose of
3 constructing water lines in a county with a population greater than
4 one hundred fifty thousand (150,000) and less than two hundred
5 thousand (200,000) according to the latest Federal Decennial Census
6 and located in a community not adjacent to a major roadway
7 designated as an interstate.
8 SECTION 3. There is hereby appropriated to the Oklahoma Water
9 Resources Board from any monies not otherwise appropriated from the
10 Progressing Rural Economic Prosperity Fund of the State Treasury
11 created in Section 256 of Title 62 of the Oklahoma Statutes, the sum
12 of Two Hundred Thousand Dollars ($200,000.00) for the purpose of
13 establishing grant programs that facilitate the design,
14 construction, and maintenance of water and wastewater
15 infrastructure, and to improve the condition of publicly owned,
16 deficient dams regulated by the Oklahoma Water Resources Board.
17 SECTION 4. This act shall become effective July 1, 2025.
18 SECTION 5. It being immediately necessary for the preservation
19 of the public peace, health or safety, an emergency is hereby
20 declared to exist, by reason whereof this act shall take effect and
21 be in full force from and after its passage and approval.
